{
  "texts": [
    "Interdisciplinary collaborations extend beyond the realms of science and technology into areas such as culinary arts, psychology, and marketing (Singh 2024).",
    "Involving chefs in research can create new flavor combinations that are not only innovative but also culturally relevant, appealing to diverse consumer bases.",
    "Chefs bring practical experience and creative insights that can inform scientific investigations, leading to the development of products that are both appealing and feasible for mass production.",
    "Psychologists can contribute by helping decipher consumer behavior patterns related to sensory experiences, identifying factors that influence taste and aroma preferences.",
    "This understanding is critical for tailoring products to meet consumer expectations and can inform marketing strategies aimed at enhancing customer engagement."
  ]
}